Introduction

Hello, my name is Ethan Wang-So. I am a student, programmer, and web designer. I am currently a second year student, majoring in Computer Science, at the New Jersey Institute of Technology. I have had a strong interest in software and coding since I was in high school. I took part in a school coding competition, where my team and I worked on an eye tracking browser extension. Currently, I work as a classroom assistant for the Computer Science Department at the New Jersey Institute of Technology. You can read more about my education and work experience below.



I am looking for any internship or co-op opportunities. I currently live in the New York/New Jersey area, but I am always willing to travel for work.

Education

I currently attend the New Jersey Institute of Technology located in Newark, New Jersey. I am a second year computer science major. I am involved with the Association for Computing Machinery and Filipinos In Newark Engaging In Socio-Cultural Traditions. I did research on campus in the virtual reality facility under Dr. Margarita Vinnikov. The research focused on 3-D Medical Ontology visualization in a Virtual Reality environment. In addition to this, I work as a Teacher's Assistant in the computer science department.



I graduated high school at St. Peter's Preparatory School in Jersey City, New Jersey.

Skills & Experience

I am knowledgeable in several programming languages such as Python, Java, C#, C++, PHP, and Javascript. I am also well versed in frameworks and libraries such as Django and React. As mentioned under the Education section, I work as a Teacher's Assistant in the computer science department. I mainly assist in teaching Python to first year students.
